  <entry>
    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/re-generate-an-id-number-in-sap-build-process-automation/qaq-p/13983362/comment-id/4898729#M4898729</id>
    <title>Re: Generate an ID number in SAP Build Process Automation</title>
    <updated>2025-01-12T07:48:38.956000+01:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Dan_Wroblewski</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/72</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;The Script Task has some constraints, described here: &lt;A href="https://help.sap.com/docs/build-process-automation/sap-build-process-automation/restrictions-on-scripting" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"&gt;https://help.sap.com/docs/build-process-automation/sap-build-process-automation/restrictions-on-scripting&lt;/A&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;One of them is no Functions, so that script will not work.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;The following script worked for me, modified from&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/44747"&gt;@arroyoweisson&lt;/a&gt;'s script.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;pre class="lia-code-sample language-javascript"&gt;&lt;code&gt;var length = 15;
var timestamp = Date.now().toString();
var randomPart = '';
var characters = '0123456789';
var charactersLength = characters.length;
var i;
for (i = 0; i &amp;lt; length - timestamp.length; i++) {
	randomPart += characters.charAt(Math.floor(Math.random() * charactersLength));
}
$.context.custom.mynumber = timestamp + randomPart;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;I created a custom variable called "mynumber", to which I return the number (instead of using return).&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;For your simpler one (though you get characters because of radix 36):&lt;/P&gt;&lt;pre class="lia-code-sample language-javascript"&gt;&lt;code&gt;var uniqueID = new Date().getTime().toString() + Math.random().toString(36).substring(2, 10);
$.context.custom.mynumber = uniqueID;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;P&gt;HTH&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;P.S.: I don't see how this will get you a sequence number, though it will give you numbers going higher.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-unicode-emoji" title=":grinning_cat_face:"&gt;😺&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/re-generate-an-id-number-in-sap-build-process-automation/qaq-p/13983362/comment-id/4898729#M4898729"/>
    <published>2025-01-12T07:48:38.956000+01:00</published>
  </entry>
  <entry>
    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/re-sap-build-apps-delete-item-persistent-storage/qaq-p/13983363/comment-id/4898730#M4898730</id>
    <title>Re: SAP Build Apps - Delete Item Persistent Storage</title>
    <updated>2025-01-12T08:04:00.893000+01:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Dan_Wroblewski</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/72</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;&lt;a href="https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/1925878"&gt;@Paull1&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;It can be a little confusing how they implemented it.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;First, no matter what you define as your fields for on-device storage, you can create a record with whatever you want. The definition you create for your entity is for defining a schema in your app, but the "storage" on your device is not validating what you send it against this schema. It is not like a database.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Second, the ID field is auto generated behind the scenes by Build Apps when you create a record on device. So you could delete the ID field from the schema, it will still be generated. And you do not get this field in the create record because you do not need to generate it.&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/re-sap-build-apps-delete-item-persistent-storage/qaq-p/13983363/comment-id/4898730#M4898730"/>
    <published>2025-01-12T08:04:00.893000+01:00</published>
  </entry>
